  "prompt": "If I have someone blocked on Instagram, and view their story, can they see I viewed it?",
  "response": "When you **block someone on Instagram**, it creates a barrier between your account and theirs. Here's how blocking affects viewing Instagram Stories:\n\n1. **Mutual Visibility Restrictions:**\n   - **You Cannot See Their Content:** Once you block someone, you won't be able to view their profile, posts, or Stories.\n   - **They Cannot See Your Content:** Similarly, the person you've blocked won't be able to see your profile, posts, or Stories.\n\n2. **Story Views:**\n   - **No Viewing While Blocked:** Since blocking prevents you from accessing their content altogether, you **cannot view their Stories** while they are blocked.\n   - **No Notification of Views:** Even if you somehow access their Stories through indirect means (which is generally not possible through Instagram's standard app), Instagram does not notify users of Story views from accounts that are blocked.\n\n3. **Unblocking Considerations:**\n   - **Temporary Unblock:** If you choose to **temporarily unblock** someone to view their Stories, be aware that any Story views made during that period would be visible to them.\n   - **Privacy After Re-Blocking:** Once you re-block the person, mutual visibility restrictions are restored, and they won\u2019t have access to your content moving forward.\n\n4. **Using Alternative Methods:**\n   - **Third-Party Tools:** Avoid using unauthorized third-party apps or methods to view Stories of blocked users. These can compromise your account's security and violate Instagram\u2019s terms of service.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **If you have someone blocked on Instagram, you cannot view their Stories.** Consequently, they cannot see you viewed their Stories because the blocking mechanism prevents any interaction or visibility between your accounts.\n\nIf you have any other questions about Instagram features or privacy settings, feel free to ask!",
